may%20reduce%20the%20risk%20of%20serious%20diseases%2C%20including%20some%20cancers%2C%20a%20new%20research%20analysis%20predicts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20eating%2030%25%20less%20processed%20meat%20alone%2C%20the%20US%20could%20reduce%20the%20rate%20of%20diabetes%2C%20heart%20disease%2C%20and%20colon%20cancer%20by%20as%20many%20as%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20cases%2C%20according%20to%20the%20study%20published%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thelancet.com%2Fjournals%2Flanplh%2Farticle%2FPIIS2542-5196(24)00118-9%2Ffulltext%23%2520%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Lancet%20Planetary%20Health%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Edinburgh%20and%20the%20University%20of%20North%20Carolina%2C%20Chapel%20Hill%2C%20developed%20a%20simulation%20tool%20based%20on%20CDC%20health%20data%20to%20estimate%20how%20a%20simple%20dietary%20change%20might%20affect%20disease%20rates%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProcessed%20meat%20has%20long%20been%20thought%20to%20be%20a%20culprit%20in%20chronic%20illnesses%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fred-meat-and-poultry-linked-to-heart-disease-risk-2020-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eheart%20disease%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Bacon%2C%20sausage%2C%20and%20ham%20contain%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprocessed-meat-increases-cancer-risk-what-to-know-2018-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreservatives%20called%20nitrates%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20previous%20evidence%20has%20linked%20to%20higher%20odds%20of%20developing%20certain%20cancers.%20Red%20meat%20and%20processed%20meats%20have%20also%20been%20linked%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fred-meat-intake-type-2-diabetes-risk-linked-harvard-study-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigher%20risk%20of%20diabetes%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20study%20could%20help%20researchers%20understand%20the%20potential%20benefits%20of%20cutting%20back%20on%20processed%20meat%20and%20how%20much%20it%20would%20take%20to%20make%20a%20difference.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20calculated%20that%20if%20Americans%20reduced%20their%20processed%20meat%20consumption%20by%20about%20a%20third%20(the%20equivalent%20of%20about%2010%20slices%20of%20bacon%20a%20week)%2C%20there%20would%20be%20significantly%20fewer%20cases%20of%20some%20of%20the%20leading%20causes%20of%20death%20over%20the%20next%20decade.%20Specifically%2C%20there%20would%20be%20about%20352%2C900%20fewer%20cases%20of%20diabetes%2C%2092%2C500%20fewer%20cases%20of%20heart%20disease%2C%20and%2053%2C300%20fewer%20cases%20of%20colorectal%20cancer%2C%20according%20to%20the%20estimate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20also%20found%20that%20eating%20less%20red%20meat%20could%20reduce%20rates%20of%20illness%20even%20more.%20However%2C%20more%20research%20is%20needed%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fred-meat-diet-unhealthy-as-processed-meat-study-2021-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunprocessed%20red%20meat%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20steak%2C%20as%20some%20studies%20have%20suggested%20that%2C%20in%20moderation%2C%20it%20may%20be%20less%20harmful%20than%20processed%20meat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20important%20caveat%20to%20the%20study%20is%20that%20the%20potential%20health%20benefits%20of%20cutting%20out%20processed%20meat%20also%20depend%20on%20what%20you%20replace%20it%20with.%20Some%20evidence%20suggests%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fplant-based-upf-processed-linked-heart-disease-death-study-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplant-based%20processed%20foods%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20meat%20substitutes%2C%20are%20also%20linked%20to%20a%20higher%20risk%20of%20illness%20and%20early%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20contrast%2C%20diets%20high%20in%20unprocessed%20whole%20foods%20such%20as%20grains%2C%20vegetables%2C%20legumes%2C%20fruits%2C%20nuts%2C%20and%20seeds%20have%20been%20linked%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flongevity-diet-food-list-cheap-easy-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elonger%2C%20healthier%20life%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20food%20choices%20also%20matter%20for%20the%20environment%2C%20according%20to%20Lindsay%20Jaacks%2C%20coauthor%20of%20the%20study%20and%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Edinburgh.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fswitch-from-meat-to-meatless-diet-environmental-benefits-2019-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMeat%20production%20is%20a%20notorious%20contributor%20to%20greenhouse%20gases%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20uses%20a%20huge%20amount%20of%20natural%20resources%2C%20such%20as%20land%20and%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20findings%20of%20the%20latest%20study%20add%20to%20a%20growing%20body%20of%20evidence%20that%20eating%20more%20sustainably%20is%20also%20good%20for%20our%20human%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20clear%20win-win%20for%20people%20and%20planet%2C%26quot%3B%20Jaacks%20said%20in%20a%20press%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freducing-processed-meat-intake-lower-disease-risk-study-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720136096000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F668724b31f0c1cd6d731aa7a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freducing-processed-meat-intake-lower-disease-risk-study-2024-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Cutting%20out%20as%20few%20as%2010%20slices%20of%20bacon%20per%20week%20could%20help%20prevent%20thousands%20of%20cases%20of%20cancer%2C%20diabetes%2C%20and%20heart%20disease%2C%20a%20new%20study%20predicts.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22glandsverk%40insider.com%20(Gabby%20Landsverk)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.co