inent%20ministerial%20positions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E-%20Deputy%20Prime%20Minister%3A%20Angela%20Rayner%20-%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERayner%2C%2044%2C%20is%20an%20outlier%20in%20a%20country%20long%20dominated%20by%20a%20ruling%20class%20disproportionately%20educated%20at%20private%20schools%20and%20Oxford%20and%20Cambridge%20universities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20grew%20up%20in%20social%20housing%20in%20northern%20England%2C%20left%20school%20without%20a%20degree%20and%20became%20a%20single%20mother%20at%2016.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20trade%20unionist%20before%20being%20elected%20to%20parliament%20in%202015%2C%20she%20was%20elected%20as%20Labour's%20number%20two%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20left-wing%20background%20and%20straight-talking%20style%20--%20complete%20with%20strong%20northern%20accent%20--%20contrasts%20with%20Starmer's%20more%20staid%20public%20persona.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20smooths%20off%20my%20rough%20edges.%20I%20bring%20him%20out%20of%20his%20shell%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20has%20famously%20said%20of%20their%20partnership.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20well%20as%20being%20deputy%20prime%20minister%20--%20filling%20in%20for%20Starmer%20at%20weekly%20parliamentary%20questions%20when%20he%20is%20unable%20to%20attend%20--%20Rayner%20would%20be%20responsible%20for%20housing%20policy%20and%20tackling%20regional%20inequalities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E-%20Finance%3A%20Rachel%20Reeves%20-%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20Bank%20of%20England%20economist%20is%20in%20line%20to%20become%20the%20first%20female%20Chancellor%20of%20the%20Exchequer%2C%20living%20next%20door%20to%20Starmer%20at%2011%20Downing%20Street.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReeves%2C%2045%2C%20has%20called%20that%20prospect%20shattering%20%26quot%3Bthe%20last%20glass%20ceiling%20in%20politics%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20central%20figure%20in%20Labour%20efforts%20over%20the%20last%20four%20years%20to%20regain%20the%20electorate's%20trust%20on%20economic%20issues%2C%20she%20insists%20it%20is%20now%20%26quot%3Bthe%20natural%20party%20of%20British%20business%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUsing%20her%20reputation%20for%20economic%20competence%2C%20Londoner%20Reeves%2C%20whose%20younger%20sister%20is%20also%20an%20MP%2C%20has%20pledged%20%26quot%3Biron%20discipline%26quot%3B%20on%20public%20finances.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20child%20chess%20champion%2C%20an%20MP%20since%202010%2C%20has%20vowed%20to%20be%20both%20%26quot%3Bpro-worker%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bpro-business%26quot%3B%20in%20her%20role%20overseeing%20the%20public%20purse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E-%20Foreign%20affairs%3A%20David%20Lammy%20-%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELammy%2C%2051%2C%20a%20black%20lawmaker%20descended%20from%20slaves%2C%20has%20honed%20his%20vision%20for%20UK%20diplomacy%20with%20dozens%20of%20foreign%20trips%20in%20the%20past%20two%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20has%20argued%20that%20the%20foreign%20ministry%20needs%20to%20%26quot%3Brediscover%20the%20art%20of%20grand%20strategy%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20post-Brexit%20era.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELammy%2C%20an%20MP%20since%20the%20age%20of%2027%20in%202000%2C%20is%20likely%20to%20steer%20Britain%20towards%20closer%20EU%20ties%20--%20no%20easy%20task%20with%20both%20Brussels%20and%20Eurosceptic%20Britons%20reticent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20will%20also%20likely%20face%20pressure%20from%20Labour's%20left%20flank%20over%20issues%20including%20its%20policy%20towards%20Israel%20and%20its%20war%20against%20Hamas%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20friend%20of%20former%20US%20President%20Barack%20Obama%2C%20Lammy%20may%20also%20have%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20possible%20White%20House%20return%20of%20Donald%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20once%20described%20Trump%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bneo-Nazi%20sympathising%20sociopath%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bprofound%20threat%20to%20the%20international%20order%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E-%20Home%20A