%20Back%20To%20Power%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EUK%20Labour%20leader%20Keir%20Starmer%20is%20an%20ex-human%20rights%20lawyer%20and%20public%20prosecutor%20who%20will%20have%20to%20focus%20his%20relentless%20work%20ethic%20and%20methodical%20mind%20to%20fixing%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20exit%20polls%20are%20confirmed%2C%20at%2061%2C%20Starmer%20will%20be%20the%20oldest%20person%20to%20become%20British%20prime%20minister%20in%20almost%20half%20a%20century%20--%20and%20comes%20just%20nine%20years%20since%20he%20was%20first%20elected%20to%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20married%20father-of-two%20is%20unlike%20most%20modern%20politicians%3A%20he%20had%20a%20long%20and%20distinguished%20career%20before%20becoming%20an%20MP%20and%20his%20views%20are%20rooted%20in%20pragmatism%20rather%20than%20ideology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20must%20return%20politics%20to%20service%2C%26quot%3B%20Starmer%20said%20repeatedly%20during%20the%20campaign%2C%20promising%20to%20put%20%26quot%3Bcountry%20first%2C%20party%20second%26quot%3B%20following%2014%20chaotic%20years%20of%20Conservative%20rule%20under%20five%20different%20prime%20ministers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20mantra%20chimes%20with%20supporters'%20lauding%20of%20him%20as%20a%20managerial%20safe%20pair%20of%20hands%20who%20will%20approach%20life%20in%20Downing%20Street%20the%20same%20way%20he%20did%20his%20legal%20career%3A%20seriously%20and%20forensically.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDetractors%2C%20though%2C%20label%20him%20an%20uninspiring%20opportunist%20who%20regularly%20shifts%20position%20on%20an%20issue%20and%20who%20has%20failed%20to%20spell%20out%20a%20clear%20and%20defining%20vision%20for%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFootball-mad%20Starmer%2C%20a%20devoted%20Arsenal%20fan%2C%20has%20struggled%20to%20shed%20his%20public%20image%20as%20buttoned-up%20and%20boring%20and%20only%20recently%20started%20to%20appear%20more%20at%20ease%20in%20the%20public%20spotlight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESupporters%20admit%20that%20he%20fails%20to%20ooze%20the%20charisma%20of%20more%20flashy%20predecessors%20like%20Boris%20Johnson%2C%20but%20say%20that%20therein%20lies%20his%20appeal%3A%20a%20reassuring%20and%20strait-laced%20presence%20following%20the%20turbulent%2C%20self-serving%20years%20of%20Tory%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20his%20grey%20quiff%20and%20black-rimmed%20glasses%20--%20Starmer%2C%20named%20after%20Labour's%20founding%20father%20Keir%20Hardie%20--%20is%20also%20the%20centre-left%20party's%20most%20working-class%20leader%20in%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20dad%20was%20a%20toolmaker%2C%20my%20mum%20was%20a%20nurse%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20tells%20voters%20often%2C%20countering%20depictions%20by%20opponents%20that%20he%20is%20the%20epitome%20of%20a%20smug%2C%20liberal%2C%20London%20elite.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStarmer's%20purging%20of%20left-wingers%20from%20his%20party%20highlights%20a%20ruthless%20side%20that%20has%20propelled%20him%20to%20Britain's%20highest%20political%20office%2C%20but%20he%20is%20said%20to%20be%20funny%20in%20private%20and%20loyal%20to%20his%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20has%20pledged%20to%20maintain%20his%20habit%20of%20not%20working%20after%206%3A00%20pm%20on%20a%20Friday%20to%20spend%20time%20with%20his%20wife%20Victoria%2C%20who%20works%20as%20an%20occupational%20therapist%20in%20the%20National%20Health%20Service%2C%20and%20their%20two%20teenage%20children%2C%20who%20he%20does%20not%20name%20in%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20something%20extraordinary%20in%20him%20still%20being%20quite%20normal%2C%26quot%3B%20Starmer's%20biographer%20Tom%20Baldwin%20wrote%20in%20the%20Guardian.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETop%20Lawyer%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBorn%20on%20September%202%2C%201962%2C%20Keir%20Rodney%20Starmer%20was%20raised%20in%20a%20cramped%2C%20pebble-dashed%20semi-detached%20house%20on%20the%20outskirts%20of%20London%20by%20a%20seriously%20ill%20mother%20and%20an%20emotionally%20distant%20father.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20had%20three%20siblings%2C%20one%20of%20whom%20had%20learning%20difficulties.%20His%20parents%20were%20animal%20lovers%20who%20rescued%20donkeys.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20talented%20musician%2C%20Starmer%20had%20violin%20lessons%20at%20school%20with%20Norman%20Cook%2C%20the%20former%20Housemartins%20bassist%20who%20became%20DJ%20Fatboy%20Slim.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20legal%20studies%20at%20the%20universities%20of%20Leeds%20and%20Oxford%2C%20Starmer%20turned%20his%20attention%20to%20leftist%20causes%2C%20defending%20trade%20unions%2C%20anti-McDonald's%20activists%2C%20and%20death%20row%20inmates%20abroad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20is%20friends%20with%20human%20rights%20lawyer%20Amal%20Clooney%20from%20their%20time%20together%20at%20the%20same%20legal%20practice%20and%20once%20recounted%20a%20boozy%20lunch%20he%20had%20with%20her%20and%20her%20Hollywood%20actor%20husband%20George.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202003%2C%20he%20began%20moving%20towards%20the%20establishment%2C%20shocking%20colleagues%20and%20friends%2C%20first%20with%20a%20job%20ensuring%20police%20in%20Northern%20Ireland%20complied%20with%20human%20rights%20legislation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFive%20years%20later%2C%20he%20was%20appointed%20director%20of%20public%20prosecutions%20(DPP)%20for%20England%20and%20Wales%20when%20Labour's%20Gordon%20Brown%20was%20prime%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBetween%202008%20and%202013%2C%20he%20oversaw%20the%20prosecution%20of%20MPs%20for%20abusing%20their%20expenses%2C%20journalists%20for%20phone-hacking%2C%20and%20young%20rioters%20involved%20in%20unrest%20across%20England.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20knighted%20by%20Queen%20Elizabeth%20II%2C%20but%20rarely%20uses%20the%20prefix%20%26quot%3BSir%26quot%3B%2C%20and%20in%202015%20was%20elected%20as%20a%20member%20of%20parliament%2C%20representing%20a%20seat%20in%20left-leaning%20north%20London.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJust%20weeks%20before%20he%20was%20elected%2C%20his%20mother%20die