%20Starmer%2C%20the%20Labour%20Party's%20candidate%20and%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20opposition.%20Mr%20Starmer%20is%20not%20a%20firebrand%20politician%2C%20but%20the%20Labour%20Party%20believes%20his%20steady%20and%20dependable%20leadership%20is%20exactly%20what%20Britain%20needs%20after%2014%20years%20of%20Conservative%20rule.%20At%2061%2C%20Mr%20Starmer%20is%20favourite%20to%20win%20the%20upcoming%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHere%20are%20some%20facts%20about%20Keir%20Starmer%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E1.%20Keir%20Starmer%20was%20born%20on%20September%202%2C%201962%2C%20in%20Oxted%2C%20Surrey%2C%20in%20a%20working-class%20family.%20His%20mother%2C%20a%20dedicated%20NHS%20nurse%2C%20battled%20a%20rare%20and%20severe%20case%20of%20rheumatoid%20arthritis%2C%20while%20his%20father%20worked%20as%20a%20toolmaker.%20Mr%20Starmer%20attended%20Reigate%20Grammar%20School%20and%20was%20the%20first%20in%20his%20family%20to%20attend%20university.%20He%20studied%20Law%20at%20Leeds%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E2.%20Before%20he%20ventured%20into%20politics%2C%20Mr%20Starmer%20was%20a%20distinguished%20human%20rights%20defence%20lawyer.%20Dubbed%20a%20%26quot%3Blefty%20lawyer%26quot%3B%20for%20his%20commitment%20to%20social%20justice%2C%20he%20began%20his%20career%20in%201987%20as%20a%20barrister%20and%20co-founded%20Doughty%20Street%20Chambers%20in%201990.%20He%20specialised%20in%20human%20rights%20cases%2C%20representing%20clients%20through%20legal%20aid%20and%20pro%20bono%20work.%20His%20expertise%20earned%20him%20a%20Queen's%20Counsel%20(QC)%20appointment%20in%202002%20and%20recognition%20as%20QC%20of%20the%20Year.%20Mr%20Starmer%20represented%20the%20%26quot%3BMcLibel%20Two%26quot%3B%20in%20their%20landmark%20defamation%20suit%20against%20McDonald's.%20He%20also%20travelled%20to%20the%20Caribbean%20and%20Africa%20to%20represent%20defendants%20facing%20the%20death%20penalty.%20He%20also%20challenged%20the%20Tony%20Blair%20government's%20invasion%20of%20Iraq%2C%20drafting%20legal%20arguments%20against%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E3.%20Mr%20Starmer%20was%20the%20legal%20advisor%20to%20the%20Northern%20Ireland%20Policing%20Board%20for%20five%20years%20from%202003%20to%202008.%20This%20was%20a%20critical%20time%20in%20the%20region's%20history%2C%20following%20the%20Good%20Friday%20Agreement%20in%201998%2C%20which%20was%20a%20significant%20step%20towards%20peace%20after%20decades%20of%20conflict.%20During%20this%20time%2C%20he%20met%20his%20wife%2C%20Victoria%2C%20who%20was%20working%20for%20the%20National%20Health%20Service%20(NHS).%20The%20couple%20got%20married%20in%202007%20and%20have%20two%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E4.%20In%202008%2C%20Mr%20Starmer%20was%20appointed%20Director%20of%20Public%20Prosecutions%2C%20leading%20the%20Crown%20Prosecution%20Service%20and%20managing%20its%20thousands%20of%20employees.%20During%20his%20tenure%2C%20he%20handled%20several%20high-profile%20cases%2C%20including%20the%20Stephen%20Lawrence%20murder%20case.%20His%20contributions%20to%20criminal%20justice%20were%20recognised%20with%20a%20knighthood%20conferred%20by%20the%20late%20Queen%20at%20Buckingham%20Palace%20in%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E5.%20Keir%20Starmer%20entered%20politics%20in%202015%20as%20the%20MP%20for%20Holborn%20and%20St%20Pancras%2C%20quickly%20taking%20on%20key%20roles%20in%20the%20Labour%20Party.%20He%20served%20as%20Shadow%20Immigration%20Minister%20from%202015%20to%202016.%20Following%20Jeremy%20Corbyn's%20resignation%20in%202019%2C%20Mr%20Starmer%20was%20elected%20the%20Labour%20Party%20leader%20in%202020.%20Mr%20Starmer%20promised%20a%20culture%20change%3B%20his%20mantra%20--%20the%20country%20before%20the%20party.%20He%20opposed%20Britain's%20decision%20to%20leave%20the%20European%20Union%20but%20clarified%20that%20a%20Labour%20government%20would%20not%20rejoin%20the%20group%2C%20which%20now%20has%2027%20members.%20If%20elected%20as%20the%20country's%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20Mr%20Starmer%20promises%20to%20bring%20stability%20and%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Labour%20Party's%20manifesto%20focuses%20on%20key%20initiatives%20such%20as%20hiring%206%2C500%20new%20teachers%2C%20expanding%20childcare%20and%20providing%20free%20breakfast%20clubs%20in%20primary%20schools.%20They%20aim%20to%20improve%20economic%20security%20by%20creating%20more%20stable%20jobs%2C%20reforming%20Universal%20Credit%20and%20strengthening%20housing%20regulations.%20The%20manifesto%20also%20talks%20about%20support%20for%20mental%20health%20in%20schools%2C%20reforming%20social%20care%20and%20advancing%20equality%20for%20women%2C%20ethnic%20minorities%2C%20disabled%20individuals%20and%20the%20LGBT%2B%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720119720000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-07%2Fdj88j8eo_keir-starmer-afp-_625x300_04_July_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwho-is-keir-starmer-the-labour-party-leader-favourite-to-replace-pm-rishi-sunak-5989167%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20May%202024%2C%20British%20Prime%20Minister%20Rishi%20Sunak%20made%20a%20surprise%20snap%20election%20announcement.%20Now%2C%20the%20UK%20will%20vote%20on%20July%204%20and%20the%20focus%2C%20apart%20from%20the%20Prime%20Minister's%20Conservative%20Party%2C%20is%20on%20Keir%20Starmer%2C%20the%20Labour%20Party's%20candidate.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwho-is-keir-starmer-the-labour-party-leader-favourite-to-replace-pm-rishi-sunak-5989167%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwho-is-keir-starmer-the-labour-party-leader-favourite-to-replace-pm-rishi-sunak-5989167%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwho-is-keir-starmer-the-labour-party-leader-favourite-to-replace-pm-rishi-sunak-5989167%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Nawaz%20initially%20ca