20party%20a%20landslide%20win%20and%20end%20nearly%20a%20decade-and-a-half%20of%20Conservative%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20national%20ballot%20since%20Boris%20Johnson%20won%20the%20Tories%20a%20decisive%20victory%20in%202019%20follows%20Prime%20Minister%20Rishi%20Sunak's%20surprise%20call%20to%20hold%20an%20election%20six%20months%20earlier%20than%20required.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20gamble%20looks%20set%20to%20backfire%20spectacularly%2C%20with%20polls%20throughout%20the%20six-week%20campaign%20--%20and%20for%20the%20last%20two%20years%20--%20pointing%20to%20a%20heavy%20defeat%20for%20his%20right-wing%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20would%20almost%20certainly%20put%20Labour%20leader%20Keir%20Starmer%2C%2061%2C%20in%20Downing%20Street%2C%20as%20leader%20of%20the%20largest%20party%20in%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECentre-left%20Labour%20is%20projected%20to%20win%20its%20first%20general%20election%20since%202005%20by%20historic%20proportions%2C%20with%20a%20flurry%20of%20election-eve%20polls%20all%20forecasting%20its%20biggest-ever%20victory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Starmer%20was%20taking%20nothing%20for%20granted%20as%20he%20urged%20voters%20not%20to%20stay%20at%20home.%20%26quot%3BBritain's%20future%20is%20on%20the%20ballot%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20change%20will%20only%20happen%20if%20you%20vote%20for%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E'People%20are%20not%20satisfied'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVoting%20began%20at%207%3A00%20am%20(0600%20GMT)%20in%20more%20than%2040%2C000%20polling%20stations%20across%20the%20country%2C%20from%20church%20halls%2C%20community%20centres%20and%20schools%20to%20more%20unusual%20venues%20such%20as%20pubs%20and%20even%20a%20ship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESunak%20was%20among%20the%20early%20birds%2C%20casting%20his%20ballot%20at%20his%20Richmond%20and%20Northallerton%20constituency%20in%20Yorkshire%2C%20northern%20England.%20Starmer%20voted%20around%20two%20hours%20later%20in%20his%20north%20London%20seat%2C%20shortly%20before%20Liberal%20Democrat%20leader%20Ed%20Davey.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20voters%20told%20AFP%20they%20were%20disillusioned%20but%20still%20planned%20to%20exercise%20their%20democratic%20right%20to%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20no%20confidence%20in%20any%20party.%20They%20are%20not%20good%20enough%20to%20run%20the%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Robin%20Moore%2C%20a%2060-year-old%20architect%20in%20Rotherhithe%20in%20east%20London.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%2020-year-old%20university%20student%2C%20who%20asked%20to%20be%20identified%20just%20by%20her%20first%20name%20Barakot%2C%20was%20more%20optimistic%2C%20however.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLots%20of%20things%20are%20going%20on%2C%20the%20cost-of-living%20crisis%2C%20being%20able%20to%20buy%20a%20house%20is%20so%20hard.%20It's%20the%20right%20moment%20to%20vote%2C%20hopefully%20to%20get%20the%20right%20people%20in%26quot%3B%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20good%20for%20everyone%20if%20we%20see%20some%20changes%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVoting%20closes%20at%2010%3A00%20pm%20(2100%20GMT).%20Broadcasters%20then%20announce%20exit%20polls%2C%20which%20typically%20provide%20an%20accurate%20picture%20of%20how%20the%20main%20parties%20have%20performed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResults%20from%20the%20UK's%20650%20constituencies%20trickle%20in%20overnight%2C%20with%20the%20winning%20party%20expected%20to%20hit%20326%20seats%20--%20the%20threshold%20for%20a%20parliamentary%20majority%20--%20as%20dawn%20breaks%20Friday.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolls%20suggest%20voters%20will%20punish%20the%20Tories%20after%2014%20years%20of%20often%20chaotic%20rule%20and%20could%20oust%20a%20string%20of%20government%20ministers%2C%20with%20talk%20that%20even%20Sunak's%20seat%20might%20not%20be%20safe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20would%20make%20him%20the%20first%20sitting%20prime%20minister%20not%20to%20retain%20his%20seat%20in%20a%20general%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20appreciate%20people%20have%20frustrations%20with%20our%20party%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20conceded%20on%20Wednesday.%20%26quot%3BBut%20tomorrow's%20vote...%20is%20a%20vote%20about%20the%20future.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EEndorsements%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESunak%2C%2044%2C%20is%20widely%20seen%20as%20having%20run%20a%20dismal%20campaign%2C%20with%20anger%20over%20his%20decision%20to%20leave%20D-Day%20commemorations%20in%20France%20early%20the%20standout%20moment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20new%20blows%20Wednesday%2C%20The%20Sun%20newspaper%20switched%20allegiance%20to%20Labour%20--%20a%20key%20endorsement%20given%20the%20tabloid%20has%20backed%20the%20winner%20at%20every%20election%20for%20several%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20follows%20The%20Financial%20Times%2C%20The%20Economist%20and%20The%20Sunday%20Times%20as%20well%20as%20traditionally%20left-leaning%20papers%20The%20Guardian%20and%20The%20Daily%20Mirror%2C%20also%20endorsing%20the%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20three%20large-scale%20surveys%20indicated%20Labour%20was%20on%20the%20brink%20of%20a%20record%20victory%2C%20with%20the%20Tories%20set%20for%20their%20worst-ever%20result%20and%20the%20centrist%20Liberal%20Democrats%20resurgent%20in%20third.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYouGov%2C%20Focaldata%20and%20More%20in%20Common%20all%20projected%20Labour%20would%20secure%20at%20least%20430%20seats%2C%20topping%20the%20418%20under%20Tony%20Blair%20in%201997.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Conservatives%20could%20plunge%20to%20a%20record%20low%20of%20less%20than%20127%2C%20the%20trio%20predicted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Lib%20Dems%20were%20tipped%20to%20scoop%20dozens%20of%20seats%20--%20up%20from%20their%20current%20tally%20of%2015%20--%20while%20Nigel%20Farage's%20anti-immigrant%20Reform%20UK%20party%20was%20set%20to%20win%20a%20handful.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYouGov%20and%20More%20in%20Common%20both%20forecast%20the%20Brexit%20figurehead%20would%20finally%20become%20an%20MP%20at%20the%20eighth%20time%20of%20asking.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Decade%20of%20national%20renewal'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20predictions%20are%20accurate%2C%20Sunak%20will%20on%20Friday%20visit%20head%20of%20state%20King%20Charles%20III%20to%20tender%20his%20resignation%20as%20prime%20minister.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStarmer%20would%20meet%20the%20monarch%20shortly%20after%20to%20take%20up%20his%20invitation%20to%20head%20the%20next%20government%20--%20and%20become%20prime%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Labour%20leader%20would%20then%20travel%20to%20Downing%20Street%20--%20the%20office%20and%20residence%20of%20British%20leaders%20--%20where%20he%20would%20be%20expected%20to%20deliver%20a%20speech%20before%20making%20ministerial%20appointments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20would%20cap%20a%20remarkable%20political%20rise%20for%20the%20former%20human%20rights%20lawyer%20and%20chief%20prosecutor%2C%20first%20elected%20an%20MP%20in%202015.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20has%20promised%20a%20%26quot%3Bdecade%20of%20national%20renewal%26quot%3B%20but%20faces%20a%20daunting%20task%20revitalising%20creaking%20public%20services%20and%20a%20flatlining%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720116240000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-07%2Fcguv7cb_labour-party-uk_625x300_04_July_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Flabour-party-tipped-for-landslide-win-as-uk-votes-in-historic-polls-6032539%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Britain%20voted%20Thursday%20in%20a%20general%20election%20that%20polls%20predict%20will%20hand%20the%20opposition%20Labour%20party%20a%20landslide%20win%20and%20end%20nearly%20a%20decade-and-a-half%20of%20Conservative%20rule.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C