%20a%20yard%20sign%20crudely%20expressing%20her%20dissatisfaction%20with%20both%20Biden%20and%20Trump.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20her%20city%2C%20Lakeland%2C%20Tennessee%2C%20near%20Memphis%2C%20deemed%20the%20sign%20%26quot%3Bobscene%26quot%3B%20and%20fined%20her%20%2450%20a%20day.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20sued%20%E2%80%94%20and%20has%20now%20settled%2C%20with%20the%20town%20paying%20her%20around%20%2432%2C000%20in%20costs%20and%20legal%20fees.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Tennessee%20woman%20whose%20eyebrow-raising%20political%20yard%20sign%20led%20to%20her%20being%20fined%20hundreds%20of%20dollars%20won%20about%20%2432%2C000%20after%20filing%20a%20First%20Amendment%20lawsuit%20against%20her%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20year%2C%20Julie%20Pereira%20posted%20a%20sign%20in%20her%20front%20year%20saying%20%26quot%3BFuck%20'Em%20Both%202024.%26quot%3B%20But%20it%20didn't%20take%20long%20for%20neighbors%20to%20complain%20and%20for%20a%20code%20enforcement%20officer%20from%20the%20Memphis%20suburb%20of%20Lakeland%20to%20fine%20Pereira%20for%20violating%20a%20city%20law%20against%20obscene%20signs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20briefly%20censored%20her%20sign%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.courtlistener.com%2Frecap%2Fgov.uscourts.tnwd.102662%2Fgov.uscourts.tnwd.102662.1.0_1.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esued%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20month.%20On%20Wednesday%2C%20lawyers%20for%20both%20sides%20sought%20approval%20for%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.courtlistener.com%2Frecap%2Fgov.uscourts.tnwd.102662%2Fgov.uscourts.tnwd.102662.19.1.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esettlement%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20deemed%20the%20city's%20actions%20to%20be%20unconstitutional%20and%20allocated%20%2431%2C000%20for%20Pereira's%20legal%20fees%2C%20plus%20several%20hundred%20dollars%20for%20damages%20and%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBeing%20able%20to%20tell%20politicians%20to%20fuck%20themselves%20is%20a%20sacred%20American%20right%2C%26quot%3B%20Daniel%20A.%20Horwitz%2C%20one%20of%20Pereira's%20lawyers%2C%20said%20in%20an%20email%20to%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20proud%20to%20have%20protected%20Mrs.%20Pereira's%20right%20to%20express%20her%20political%20views%20and%20to%20have%20achieved%20a%20successful%20outcome%20in%20this%20important%20First%20Amendment%20case.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPereira%20said%20in%20her%20lawsuit%20that%20she's%20unhappy%20with%20both%20main%20candidates%2C%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20and%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20in%20the%20upcoming%20November%20election.%20But%20her%20election%20sign%20isn't%20the%20first%20thing%20to%20upset%20city%20officials.%20Local%20news%20station%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.localmemphis.com%2Farticle%2Fnews%2Fcommunity%2Fcity-lakeland-settles-resident-over-sign-ordinance-violation%2F522-32c312e5-9600-4503-92b9-09c9aeecbcb6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EABC24%20reported%20in%20May%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Pereira%20also%20successfully%20sued%20the%20city%20after%20it%20cited%20her%20for%20a%20Christmas%20decoration%20that%20used%20foul%20language%20in%20a%20reference%20to%20the%201989%20comedy%20film%20%26quot%3BNational%20Lampoon's%20Christmas%20Vacation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20she%20initially%20contested%20the%20violation%20over%20her%20%26quot%3BFuck%20'Em%20Both%26quot%3B%20sign%2C%20the%20judge%20said%20it%20wasn't%20clear%20that%20%26quot%3Bboth%26quot%3B%20referred%20to%20Biden%20and%20Trump%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.courtlistener.com%2Frecap%2Fgov.uscourts.tnwd.102662%2Fgov.uscourts.tnwd.102662.1.6.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etranscript%3C%2Fa%3E%20showed.%20A%20code%20enforcement%20officer%20said%20at%20least%2010%20neighbors%20had%20complained%2C%20including%20one%20person%20who%20claimed%20they%20wouldn't%20have%20bought%20a%20home%20in%20the%20area%20if%20Pereira's%20sign%20had%20been%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20also%20alluded%20to%20Pereira's%20previous%20clash%20with%20the%20city%20and%20noted%20that%20jail%20time%20was%20a%20possibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20will%20warn%20you%2C%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20see%20you%20back%20in%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20judge%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYour%20Honor%2C%20I%20do%20not%20want%20to%20see%20the%20City%20of%20Lakeland%20continue%20to%20violate%20my%20First%20Amendment%20rights%2C%26quot%3B%20Pereira%20replied.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECity%20officials%20didn't%20respond%20to%20an%20email%20made%20on%20July%204%2C%20a%20US%20holiday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftennessee-woman-obscenity-biden-trump-yard-sign-lawsuit-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720114458000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6686cd38268f62ba18a78fbc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftennessee-woman-obscenity-biden-trump-yard-sign-lawsuit-2024-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20woman%20whose%20yard%20sign%20used%20a%20curse%20word%20to%20describe%20her%20feelings%20about%20Biden%20and%20Trump%20was%20fined.%20Now%2C%20she%20won%20big%20in%20a%20lawsuit.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jnewsham%40insider.com%20(Jack%20Newsham)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A132%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftennessee-woman-obscenity-biden-trump-yard-sign-lawsuit-2024-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Jay%20Slater's%20family%20hits%20back%20at%20TikToker%20who%20has%20quit%20search%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720114380000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F06%2F1920x1080%2Fskynews-jay-slater-tenerife_6585852.jpg%3F20240619200657%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fjay-slater-tiktok-star-quits-search-and-says-hes-never-had-any-money-from-gofundme-13164027%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Jay%20Slat