e-at-risk-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMillennials%2C%20in%20particular%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20seem%20to%20be%20especially%20fond%20of%20the%20trend.%20A%20recent%20Harris%20Poll%20found%20that%20nearly%20four%20out%20of%2010%20millennial%20respondents%20admitted%20to%20taking%20time%20off%20without%20informing%20higher-ups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20what's%20a%20boss%20to%20do%20if%20he%20wants%20to%20stop%20employees%20from%20sneaking%20out%20of%20the%20office%20behind%20his%20back%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDavid%20Barkoe%2C%20the%20CEO%20and%20founder%20of%20Florida-based%20PR%20firm%20Carve%20Communications%2C%20said%20it%20all%20comes%20down%20to%20creating%20a%20culture%20of%20trust%20with%20your%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGo%20live%20your%20life%2C%20but%20get%20the%20job%20done%2C%26quot%3B%20Barkoe%20told%20Business%20Insider%20while%20describing%20his%20approach.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20going%20to%20trust%20you%20from%20minute%20one%2C%20from%20the%20moment%20I%20hire%20you%2C%20to%20just%20get%20the%20job%20done%2C%20however%20you%20feel%20best%20to%20do%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20practice%2C%20that%20culture%20takes%20a%20lot%20of%20forms.%20Sometimes%2C%20it's%20an%20employee%20working%20a%20couple%20hours%20early%20in%20the%20morning%20so%20they%20can%20sign%20off%20early%20to%20make%20their%20kid's%20swim%20meet.%20Other%20times%2C%20it's%20an%20employee%20taking%20a%20three-week%20trip%20to%20Europe%20where%20the%20first%20week%20is%20PTO%2C%20and%20the%20next%20two%2C%20they%20simply%20work%20from%20another%20time%20zone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBarkoe%20said%20the%20open%20and%20flexible%20culture%2C%20which%20is%20actively%20encouraged%20and%20practiced%20by%20higher-ups%2C%20makes%20it%20so%20employees%20do%20not%20feel%20like%20they%20need%20to%20sneak%20away%20just%20to%20get%20a%20break.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20absolutely%20culture-driven%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBarkoe%20believes%20a%20reason%20people%20are%20taking%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquiet-vacations-work-trends-culture-pto-travel-job-stress-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Equiet%20vacations%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20because%20they%20feel%20like%20their%20employer%20is%20not%20giving%20them%20trust%20and%20respect%2C%20so%20they%20just%20take%20the%20vacation%20they%20want%20anyway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20bosses%20who%20are%20worried%20having%20such%20a%20flexible%20culture%20would%20result%20in%20less%20work%20getting%20done%2C%20Barkoe%20has%20found%20the%20opposite%20to%20be%20true.%20When%20Carve%20went%20fully%20remote%20in%202020%2C%20Barkoe%20said%20he%20realized%20very%20quickly%20they%20were%20never%20going%20back%20to%20the%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20just%20working.%20People%20were%20more%20motivated%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20it%20may%20be%20different%20at%20a%20company%20with%20thousands%20of%20employees%2C%20Barkoe%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BAs%20a%20small%20organization%2C%20if%20you're%20not%20doing%20your%20job%2C%20it's%20pretty%20hard%20to%20hide.%26quot%3B%20He%20added%20that%20if%20someone%20does%20take%20advantage%2C%20then%20they're%20probably%20not%20the%20right%20person%20for%20your%20team%2C%20regardless.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAshton%20Mathai%2C%20the%20associate%20director%20of%20content%20at%20Barkoe's%20firm%2C%20told%20BI%20she%20fully%20takes%20advantage%20of%20Carve's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funlimited-pto-vacation-scam-time-off-managers-fight-burnout-culture-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunlimited%20PTO%20policy%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20work-from-anywhere%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20in%20a%20cap%20sits%20on%20a%20folding%20chair%20with%20a%20view%20of%20the%20lake%20and%20pine%20trees%20and%20works.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66857d321f0c1cd6d7314ef4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20recent%20survey%20found%20millennials%20were%20more%20likely%20than%20other%20generations%20to%20take%20time%20off%20without%20telling%20their%20bosses.%3Cp%3EMariya%20Borisova%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20Mathai%20traveled%20to%20Europe%20for%20two%20months.%20She%20took%2010%20days%20of%20PTO%20to%20start%20the%20trip%20and%20then%20spent%20the%20remainder%20of%20the%20time%20working%20from%20places%20like%20Scotland%2C%20Amsterdam%2C%20Portugal%2C%20and%20Italy.%20Because%20she%20was%20in%20a%20different%20time%20zone%2C%20she'd%20often%20work%201%20p.m.%20to%208%20p.m.%20local%20time%20and%20spend%20the%20morning%20doing%20a%20tour%20or%20going%20to%20the%20beach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20live%20my%20life%20in%20the%20morning%20and%20then%20in%20the%20afternoon%2C%20night%20I%20would%20do%20my%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMathai%20said%20before%20she%20went%2C%20her%20bosses%20told%20her%20they%20had%20total%20confidence%20in%20her%20that%20she%20would%20get%20her%20work%20done%20while%20she%20was%20gone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20wasn't%20a%20threat.%20It%20was%20truly%20total%20confidence%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20I%20kind%20of%20went%20there%20knowing%20like%20I%20want%20to%20make%20them%20proud.%20I%20want%20to%20make%20myself%20proud%20and%20do%20my%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20working%20from%20abroad%2C%20she%20said%20she%20also%20takes%20plenty%20of%20full-fledged%20PTO.%20Earlier%20this%20year%2C%20she%20traveled%20to%20India%20for%20two%20weeks%20with%20family%20and%20didn't%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20encouragement%20from%20leadership%2C%20from%20David%20himself%2C%20to%20take%20time%20off%2C%26quot%3B%20Mathai%20said%20of%20Barkoe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBarkoe%20said%20a%20lot%20of%20companies%20have%20unlimited%20PTO%20in%20t