%20million%20views%20and%2052%2C000%20likes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplatform.twitter.com%2Fwidgets.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22twitter%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThings%20I'm%20sick%20of%20hearing%20from%20my%20employees%3A%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cbr%3E-%20Can%20I%20leave%20early%20today%3Cbr%3E-%20I'll%20be%20late%20in%20the%20morning%3Cbr%3E-%20My%20child%20is%20sick%2C%20can%20I%20rush%20off%3Cbr%3E-%20I've%20got%20a%20doctor's%20appointment%20tomorrow%2C%20is%20that%20okay%3Cbr%3E-%20I'm%20going%20to%20be%20late%20back%20from%20lunch%2C%20I've%20got%20some%20things%20to%20sort%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EI%20don't%20care.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FJfkivEli07%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FJfkivEli07%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%E2%80%94%20Rob%20Dance%20(%40RobDance_)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FRobDance_%2Fstatus%2F1807767539159589026%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EJuly%201%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2293f46ea3-eb74-40fc-a3a9-66a1cea7fb8d%5C%22%3EThe%20'trust%20bucket'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKoma%20Gandy%2C%20the%20VP%20of%20business%20and%20leadership%20at%20Skillsoft%2C%20the%20corporate%20training%20platform%2C%20says%20Dance%20made%20some%20good%20points.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorkplaces%20are%20now%20multi-generational%2C%20with%20Zoomers%2C%20millennials%2C%20Gen%20Xers%2C%20and%20boomers%2C%20so%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsoft-skills-help-middle-managers-survive-the-great-unbossing-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esoft%20skills%20such%20as%20empathy%20and%20transparent%20communication%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20more%20important%20than%20ever.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrust%20and%20flexibility%20are%20a%20huge%20part%20of%20building%20an%20effective%20workplace%2C%20Gandy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20more%20traditional%20workplaces%2C%20it%20may%20be%20expected%20that%20employees%20are%20visible%2C%20attend%20all%20meetings%2C%20and%20work%20online%20for%20a%20certain%20number%20of%20hours.%20But%20according%20to%20Gandy%2C%20this%20can%20perpetuate%20a%20toxic%20cycle%20of%20people%20being%20%26quot%3Bperformative%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bbragging%26quot%3B%20about%20how%20busy%20they%20are.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBeing%20busy%20and%20effective%20or%20not%20necessarily%20the%20same%20thing%2C%26quot%3B%20Gandy%20said.%20%26quot%3BYour%20role%20is%20not%20dependent%20on%20jiggling%20a%20mouse%20every%2010%20to%2015%20minutes%20because%20some%20software%20is%20trying%20to%20track%20how%20busy%20you%20are.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGandy%20said%20giving%20employees%20the%20time%20and%20space%20to%20do%20their%20jobs%20effectively%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicromanager-boss-being-better-manager-tips-advice-2020-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewithout%20being%20micromanaged%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20like%20%26quot%3Bputting%20coins%20in%20the%20trust%20bucket.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20not%20an%20empathetic%20leader%2C%20and%20you're%20not%20putting%20coins%20in%20that%20trust%20bucket%2C%20when%20the%20time%20comes%20that%20you're%20going%20to%20need%20to%20withdraw%2C%20there's%20going%20to%20be%20nothing%20in%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20somebody%20is%20struggling%20or%20being%20dishonest%20about%20their%20time%2C%20it's%20likely%20to%20become%20clear%20in%20different%20ways%20anyway%2C%20in%20their%20quality%20of%20work%20and%20performance%2C%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220f6f466c-29e5-4aad-9304-306f865921bc%5C%22%3EThe%20dangers%20of%20undermanaging%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20every%20employee%20benefits%20from%20having%20such%20freedom.%20Junior%20staff%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20may%20prefer%20more%20structure%20and%20guidance%20on%20how%20to%20manage%20their%20time%20and%20workload.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20a%20fine%20line%20between%20giving%20employees%20more%20freedom%20and%20%26quot%3Bundermanaging%26quot%3B%20their%20performance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKevin%20Legg%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Sage%2C%20a%20company%20developing%20training%20for%20workplaces%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2023%2F08%2F16%2F3-unexpected-traits-of-bad-bosses-and-tell-tale-signs-of-dysfunction.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etold%20CNBC%20in%20an%20interview%20last%20year%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20bosses%20can%20sometimes%20fall%20into%20that%20trap%20of%20undermanging%2C%20which%20can%20be%20just%20as%20damaging%20as%20micromanaging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20medium%20term%2C%20there%20is%20resentment%20at%20annual%20reviews%20when%20folks%20are%20passed%20over%20for%20promotions%20because%20they%20never%20lived%20up%20to%20a%20standard%20they%20were%20never%20shown%2C%26quot%3B%20Legg%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20most%20part%2C%20however%2C%20research%20seems%20to%20back%20Dance's%20style%20of%20management%20as%20being%20the%20most%20effective%2C%20as%20long%20as%20employees%20still%20have%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGartner%20research%20from%20April%202025%20found%20that%20when%20employers%20go%20big%20on%20flexibility%20%E2%80%94%20and%20don't%20limit%20it%20to%20when%20and%20where%20people%20work%20%E2%80%94%20the%20share%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gartner.com%2Fen%2Farticles%2Fthe-secret-to-productive-employees-a-radical-shift-in-work-flexibility%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eemployees%20who%20are%20%26quot%3Bhigh%20performers%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20jumps%20by%2040%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2204ff6b64-1b18-4133-a0fd-06acd0b36cb2%5C%22%3EA%20mindset%20shift%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEmployees%20will%20also%20have%20to%20become%20comfortable%20with%20a%20more%20trusting%20dynamic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGandy%20said%20if%20someone%20is%20used%20to%20being%20micromanaged%20and%20overexplaining%20every%20hour%20of%20the%20day%2C%20they%20have%20to%20%26quot%3Bget%20comfortable%26quot%3B%20with%20having%20downtime%20in%20their%20calendar%20rather%20than%20being%20in%20meetings%20all%20day%2C%20every%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20going%20to%20have%20folks%20who%20default%20to%2C%20I'm%20so%20busy%2C%20I%20have%20meetings%20from%208%20a.m.%20to%205%20p.m.%2C%20and%20that%20means%20I'm%20extremely%20valuable%2C%26quot%3B%20Gandy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWell%2C%20I%20would%20also%20say%20that%20means%20you're%20extremely%20stressed%2C%20and%20you're%20going%20to%20burn%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20more%20important%20to%20show%20up%20and%20be%20impactful%20in%20specific%20places%20than%20to%20show%20up%20everywhere.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20signs%20of%20burnout%20can%20start%20subtly%2C%20such%20as%20sleeping%20in%20too%20much%20on%20the%20weekend%2C%20having%20a%20few%20too%20many%20drinks%20at%20happy%20hour%2C%20or%20developing%20unhealthy%20eating%20patterns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20want%20somebody%20who%20has%20cardiovascular%20issues%20or%20can't%20sleep%20or%20has%20an%20eating%20problem%20because%20of%20something%20you%20could%20have%20missed%20with%20just%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20investment%20in%20trust%20and%20leadership%20and%20empathy%20to%20find%20out%20what%20was%20going%20on%20with%20that%20person%2C%26quot%3B%20Gandy%20said.%20%26quot%3BRather%20than%20driving%20to%20the%20point%20where%20they%20start%20adopting%20destructive%20behaviors%20that%20affect%20themselves%20or%20affect%20the%20company.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20benefit%20of%20a%20trusting%20workplace%20is%20a%20healthier%20environment%20with%20happier%2C%20more%20enthusiastic%20people%2C%20Gandy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHealthier%20leaders%2C%20healthier%20managers%2C%20and%20healthier%20organizations%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhy%20wouldn't%20we%20want%20all%20that%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceo-viral-trust-in-employees-why-thats-a-good-thing-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720107577000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6686a3f51f0c1cd6d731a3b9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceo-viral-trust-in-employees-why-thats-a-good-thing-2024-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Rob%20Dance%20said%20he's%20tired%20of%20hearing%20his%20employees%20telling%20him%20they%20have%20to%20leave%20early%2C%20because%20he%20trusts%20them%20to%20do%20their%20jobs.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ldodgson%40insider.com%20(Lindsay%20Dodgson)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A177%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceo-viral-trust-in-employees-why-thats-a-good-thing-2024-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22British%20teacher%20jailed%20for%20sex%20with%20schoolboys%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720106862000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-111494350%2Cimgsize-354821.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fuk%2Fbritish-teacher-jailed-for-sex-with-schoolboys%2Farticleshow%2F111493867.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F111493867.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3E%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20World%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fuk%2Fbritish-teacher-jailed-for-sex-with-schoolboys%2Farticleshow%2F111493867.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2F